      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is the legal justification that the Constitution must be interpreted according to the public meaning understood by the ratifiers at the time it was adopted. This approach insists that the Constitution is a fixed document with specific, ascertainable meanings, preventing judges from imposing their own modern policy preferences. Therefore, originalists argue that fidelity to the text's original intent is the only legitimate basis for constitutional law.",
